# SSHD Log Security Analysis
# Detects common attack patterns and suspicious activities

note: Checking for suspicious SSH activities

# 1. Failed login attempts (brute force indicators)
note: Detecting failed login attempts
regexp: Failed \s+ password
generator: <<CODE
!ruby

matched_list = matched()

if matched_list.length > 0
  puts "assert: 1 failed password attempt detected"
  puts "note: Total failed attempts: #{matched_list.length}"
  puts "note: Last 10 failed login attempts:"
  last_ten = matched_list.last(10)
  last_ten.each do |entry|
    puts "note:   #{entry}"
  end
else
  puts "assert: 1 no failed attempts found"
end

CODE

# 2. Invalid user attempts
note: Detecting invalid user login attempts
regexp: Invalid \s+ user
generator: <<CODE
!ruby

matched_list = matched()

if matched_list.length > 0
  puts "assert: 1 invalid user attempts detected: #{matched_list.length} attempts"
  puts "note: Last 10 invalid user attempts:"
